@Stafer: I never really noticed that there where pedo zites on there (again, apart from pedochan)
@Thunder: @Stafer:
Zeronet zites are actually WAY more harder to take down than onion sites, where it only takes one uncovered IP address to take down the server, which is really costly, heavily depends on mistakes made by the owner and in general a really hard thing to do. On zeronet you would, even on unpopular zites do that about 20 times in a row, to take down a zite, that is not only infeasible but borderline impossible, much less a zite with 200 or 1000 peers.
